<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Squier" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Squier</orth> or <orth extent="full" opt="n">Squire,</orth> a square, a rule, a measure: <cit><quote>do not you know my lady's foot by the s.?</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.474" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 474</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>twelve foot and a half by the s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 4.4.348" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. IV, 4, 348</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>four foot by the s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 2, 13</bibl></cit>.
